:INFO
Mix and Coat in Subdued Light
Mix equal parts solution A (25 g ferric ammonium citrate per 100 ml water) and solution \
B (10 g potassium ferricyanide per 100 ml water) just before use. Working in shade or \
dim indoor light, apply a thin even coat to watercolor paper (140 lb or heavier)

:PATH
Arrange Objects or Negatives and Expose
Lay your dried coated paper on a hard board.
|
:INFO
Arrange Objects or Negatives and Expose
Lay your dried coated paper on a hard board. Place flat objects (leaves, feathers, lace, \
keys) or a printed transparency negative directly on the surface. Cover with a sheet of \
glass to hold everything flat and ensure sharp edges. Take outside into

:PATH
